      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MYAH MISS (2) hasn't raced since copping a check in the run and finishing out of the placings when a 17 length sixth (20.70) in a Grade 6 at Angle Park. With a good start should be able to take advantage of the low draw. Looks the one to beat on best. NEON BLUE (5) was safely held last time out, finishing sixth at this track over 400m behind Sebon Disco (23.85) in a Grade 6. Was in the money the start prior. Has good early speed so she should be prominent despite the squeeze draw. Great chance to atone. ASTON VERONA (1) jumped from a middle draw last time and could manage only fifth and beaten 3 lengths (20.24) at Angle Park. Safe beginner who draws ideally on the inside. Has ability and a bold showing is expected. ASTON BAKER (8) is a chance after winning last time.",
